<br>
I switched over from playing on blue servers to P v P for a total of about 100 levels (the highest character getting to 42).  I think it adds a great element of excitment to the game.  Even players who don't want to kill other players can have a good time, because they have to be on their guard for PKs and experience a lot of excitement in running through enemy territory or escaping a killer.  Lots of players however, get bad experiences early on and get discouraged.  They don't really see there being any reward to playing P v P and rationalize reasons for their disappointment, such as the people playing on P v P being &quot;psycho&quot; or the P v P system being &quot;broken.&quot;  As a result the server populations of the P v P servers are the lowest in the game.  I think something ought to be done to encourage people to try out P v P, and try it again.  <br>
<br>
I suggest instituting an experience bonus all zones in addition to the base one, for playing on P v P servers, a bonus of at least 10%, even better at 20%.  This means players will level faster.  This offsets the penalty of playing on a P v P server, where you can expect your experience to be slowed down because you cannot get experience in  P v P, and you often lose experience getting killed while in P v P (often to mobs, guards, etc on P v P servers other than Sullon), and just plain losing time by having to do corpse recoverys, etc.  Having an experience bonus will make players have an incentive to play on the P v P servers, because they won't have to spend as much time camping experience (boring) and will have more time to engage in P v P.  It will also be encouragement for people to start on Sullon even when there are higher levels in the game, because they can level faster.   <p><B>Lisboa Bixiestinger</B>
<BR>Retired level 42 rogue of Bertoxxulous<BR>

Rorer Junior<BR>
Retired level 28 Iksar Shaman and Freeport Resident<BR>
<BR>
_____, level X necromancer of Sullon Zek

